<figure><img src="http://farm6.staticflickr.com/5477/14195508274_10ea023fd4_c.jpg" alt="Death Road"><figcaption>Didn't feel like stopping before this point. Turns out death road isn't all that deadly. Fun ride though!</figcaption></figure><figure><img src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7328/14008974407_23141347b7_c.jpg" alt="Strange Mountain Face"><figcaption>This mountain face on the way to Death Road seemed odd to me.</figcaption></figure><figure><img src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7373/14195512134_6e8ebc3d3a_c.jpg" alt="Valle De La Luna Panorama"><figcaption>You can just see a little dude up atop a rock near the middle. He's playing a flute which echoes through the whole valley. Good idea, dude.</figcaption></figure><figure><img src="http://farm3.staticflickr.com/2924/14172437246_28dafa7565_c.jpg" alt="Valle De La Luna - Valley of the Moon"><figcaption>This is the valley of the moon, just south of La Paz. Erosion can do some pretty interesting things.</figcaption></figure><figure><img src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7360/14195582025_b7fd287005_c.jpg" alt="Food Tour"><figcaption>So much meat and french fries. Welcome to Bolivia!</figcaption></figure><figure><img src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7404/14008950160_6d159db715_c.jpg" alt="Llama Fetuses"><figcaption>More dead llamas. Good luck apparently! </figcaption></figure><figure><img src="http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3715/13856344385_fec9155499_c.jpg" alt="Cholitas Choking"><figcaption>Someone has to get choked by their own braids, or it isn't cholita wrestling.</figcaption></figure><figure><img src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7164/13856733654_4daa3ddfd5_c.jpg" alt="Cholita"><figcaption>This was my favorite cholita wrestler. I couldn't get enough of this cutle little lady.</figcaption></figure><figure><img src="http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3826/13856371255_25726364de_c.jpg" alt="Cholita"><figcaption></figcaption></figure><figure><img src="http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3722/13856378475_92cf0da9af_c.jpg" alt="Cholita"><figcaption></figcaption></figure><figure><img src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7111/13856389675_8468053397_c.jpg" alt="Luchador"><figcaption>Luchador wrester. This guys shape cracked me up.</figcaption></figure><figure><img src="http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3742/13856778094_1a134b9b90_c.jpg" alt="Windy Road"><figcaption>This road winds quickly down into La Paz.</figcaption></figure><figure><img src="http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3791/13856450743_6dba4f3538_c.jpg" alt="Cholita Wrestling Tickets"><figcaption></figcaption></figure><figure><img src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7176/13856460853_c027bd8115_c.jpg" alt="TV Taxi"><figcaption>This taxi plays music videos in the console. </figcaption></figure><figure><img src="http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3833/13856471663_5a26e88b60_c.jpg" alt="Tunnel"><figcaption>Tunnel on the way home one night.</figcaption></figure><figure><img src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7373/13856440735_6cb63cd84e_c.jpg" alt="Loud Music Warning"><figcaption>These signs are required by law, basically telling you how long you can be in a bar with loud music without damaging your hearing. I found it sort of funny considering everyone still smokes in bars here.</figcaption></figure><figure><img src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7280/13856827964_1b8ced599f_c.jpg" alt="Shoeshine Painter"><figcaption>Almost all of the shoeshine boys here wear ski masks, apparently it has something to do with being ashamed of their job, but it looks sort of creepy. Rather than a picture of the person, here's a picture of a mural of a person.</figcaption></figure><figure><img src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7441/13856500913_e13c676a31_c.jpg" alt="Llama Fetuses"><figcaption>These llama fetuses are supposedly for good luck.</figcaption></figure><figure><img src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7323/13742147394_3d2ec08421_c.jpg" alt="La Paz from Above"><figcaption>My first glimpse of La Paz. The number of little boxes was boggling to the eye.</figcaption></figure><figure><img src="http://farm3.staticflickr.com/2880/13741789163_99034a4f99_c.jpg" alt="La Paz from Above Panorama"><figcaption>This gets a few more in there.</figcaption></figure><figure><img src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7411/13741753925_ea06ed5418_c.jpg" alt="The Barge"><figcaption>Had to take a barge across Lake Titicaca. This was moments before the lighting and hail started. 20 Bolivianos for the ride across (a little under $3).</figcaption></figure><figure><img src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7123/13742172134_659491fa86_c.jpg" alt="Curve"><figcaption>The road curves along Titicaca.</figcaption></figure><figure><img src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7026/13741821193_217ff13cc0_c.jpg" alt="Copacabana"><figcaption>I rode around Copacabana and decided to stick to the road to La Paz.</figcaption></figure><figure><img src="http://farm3.staticflickr.com/2832/13741793055_7d17273b8d_c.jpg" alt="Silviu Florea"><figcaption>Was riding in the opposite direction of Silviu, when he stopped me to give me a gas can (to save some cash in Bolivia, because locals can buy gas for about a third of the price.). Since he was heading to Peru, and I to Bolivia we swapped SIM cards, and some stories on the side of the road. He also gave me his map of Bolivia. It was really great running into someone on the road at such a perfect time.
</figcaption></figure>